sql:
SELECT novel_title 
FROM shortlisted_nominees 
WHERE author = 'John Banville' AND language = 'English';

SELECT year, winning_novel, winner_language
FROM awards
ORDER BY year ASC;

external_knowledge:
- "golden eye" metaphorically refers to the awards given to novels; 
- "masterpieces" are the titles of the novels;
- "distinguished honors" refers to the names of the awards.

sql:
SELECT sn.author, sn.novel_title, a.award_name
FROM shortlisted_nominees sn
JOIN awards a ON sn.award_id = a.award_id;

SELECT DISTINCT s.author
FROM submissions s
WHERE s.author IN (SELECT a.winner FROM awards a);

SELECT shortlisted_nominees.author
FROM shortlisted_nominees
WHERE shortlisted_nominees.author NOT IN (
    SELECT awards.winner
    FROM awards
);

SELECT category, winner AS author, winning_novel
FROM awards
WHERE winner <> '';

external_knowledge:
- Accolades: Here refers to awards;
- Entries: Refers to submissions;
- Mean score: The average score given to entries by judges;
- Digital representations: Digital assets, including images, videos, and other media related to the awards.

- 'Explorers': refers to users who have participated in the award;
- 'set sail in the vast ocean of global Fiction': refers to users who have participated in the Fiction category of the Global award;
- 'average sea level they've navigated': refers to the average score these users have received for their submissions.

sql:
SELECT DISTINCT a.user_id, a.award_id, a.novel_title
FROM submissions a
JOIN submissions b ON a.novel_title = b.novel_title AND a.user_id = b.user_id AND a.award_id != b.award_id;

external_knowledge:
- 'Non-Fiction' refers to the category of awards for factual and non-imaginative writing;
- Average scores indicate the overall performance of users in the 'Non-Fiction' category;
- "Navigated the stormy seas" metaphorically refers to the challenges faced by users in submitting and receiving evaluations for their 'Non-Fiction' works;
- "Calm and peaceful waters" metaphorically indicates high average scores indicating success in the evaluations.
